# ci-decision-golden.json.meta — provenance sidecar for ci-decision-golden.json (#399 W1d, R4).
#
# Captures decision-level rc trajectories for the PRE-#399 ci_is_green (byte-
# identical gh-argv passthrough where the caller's `--json state -q '[.[].state]'`
# returned a per-check state array and the caller applied `length>0 and
# all(.=="SUCCESS")` on that array — captured in `old_ci_is_green_rc`) AND
# the POST-#399 ci_is_green (which captures the new `chp_ci_status`'s single
# normalized token `green|pending|failed|none` and tests
# `[[ "$token" == "green" ]]` — captured in `new_ci_is_green_rc` +
# `new_token`).
#
# The gh_stdout field is the RAW `gh pr checks --json state` payload (the
# NEW-leaf shape, `[{"state":"..."}]`). The OLD passthrough shim in the
# parity harness (tests/unit/test-w1d-ci-status-mergeable-parity.sh's
# `_drive_ci_is_green_old`) re-applies the pre-#399 caller's `-q
# '[.[].state]'` filter so the OLD ci_is_green sees the state-string array
# it historically consumed — matching production exactly.
#
# Rows are the six TC-DSAP-004 fixture classes PLUS four gh rc-quirk /
# rule-2-over-rule-3 / SKIPPED cases R2 pins:
#
#   all_success_one, all_success_many        — ≥1 SUCCESS, no other state → green (rc 0)
#   mixed_pending                            — SUCCESS + PENDING → pending (rc 1)
#   mixed_failure                            — SUCCESS + FAILURE → failed (rc 1)
#   skipped_success                          — SKIPPED + SUCCESS → pending (rc 1, SKIPPED != SUCCESS)
#   empty_array                              — [] → none (rc 1)
#   transport_error                          — gh rc≠0 + empty stdout → leaf rc≠0, ci_is_green rc 1
#   failure_and_skipped                      — rule 2 beats rule 3 (FAILURE + SKIPPED → failed)
#   cancelled_and_pending                    — CANCELLED terminal → failed (rule 2)
#   in_progress_only                         — IN_PROGRESS only → pending (rule 3)
#   rc_nonzero_valid_json_success            — gh rc-quirk: rc≠0 with parseable JSON → derive token from stdout
#   rc_nonzero_garbage_stdout                — genuine transport failure: rc≠0 + non-JSON → leaf rc≠0
#   rc_nonzero_empty_array                   — gh rc-quirk: rc≠0 + `[]` (real zero-checks PR path) → token 'none', old=1/new=1 parity (online-review r1 blocking finding on PR #410)
#
# INTENTIONAL DECISION CHANGE (single documented row):
#
#   rc_nonzero_valid_json_success — pre-#399 old_rc=1, post-#399 new_rc=0.
#   `gh pr checks` exits non-zero for the "some checks failing/pending" case
#   even when the JSON payload is well-formed. The OLD caller's
#   `if ci_states=$(chp_ci_status ...); then` fell into its else-branch,
#   ci_states='[]', gate rc 1 (false-negative not-green). The NEW leaf
#   inspects stdout, derives `green` from the parseable all-SUCCESS
#   payload → ci_is_green rc 0 (correct-green — this is what a human reading
#   the payload would say). The parity harness explicitly asserts old=1 AND
#   new=0 for this row, and the fixture's `_intentional_decision_change`
#   flag documents the divergence in-band. This is the ONE intentional
#   decision change in the W1d parity contract; every other row asserts
#   old_rc == new_rc.
#
# Regenerate (only if the OLD ci_is_green semantics are ever in dispute):
# checkout the commit immediately before #399's leaf rewrite (b13ef4b~1 or
# origin/main from the #399 base-commit era), source lib-dispatch.sh under
# the fixture harness in tests/unit/test-w1d-ci-status-mergeable-parity.sh,
# feed each row's `gh_stdout` / `gh_rc` through the passthrough
# chp_ci_status shim, and record the resulting ci_is_green rc.
